	<text_base_description>This unit is the epitome of what one would expect to see at the Hollywood Riviera, one of West Hollywood's most iconic and architecturally significant condo properties. This stunning 1954 mid-century modern masterpiece was designed by renowned architect Edward Fickett AIA and has been featured in many TV shows, movies, and commercials. This unique and open city loft-style space with high pitched beamed ceilings is in a convenient and coveted location with pool views from the front and some city and hill views from the back. This unit was altered to function as a studio which could easily be converted back to a one-bedroom with updated bathroom, massive walk-in closet and separate kitchen with window overlooking pool. This condo also has central AC, low HOA dues including EQ insurance, and building is Mills Act approved.  </text_base_description>
